column1: # Supplemental Table S2.  Genes enriched for antisense 22G-RNAs in the CSR-1 IP.  A list of 4191 genes for which there are at least 25 small RNA reads per million and an enrichment of two-fold or greater in the CSR-1 IP when compared to the wild-type Input sample.
# Reads = number of reads antisense to and overlaping exon-exon juntions of the indicated gene
column2: normalized to the number of times each sequence perfectly matches the genome.
excluding reads considered to be degradation products

column1: # Ratio is calculated as: input/(input+IP) using the normalized read -norm value
